alerts.title: Potential Domain Hijacking - company.biz
alerts.description:
The domain company.biz is pointing to unfamiliar IP addresses which do not appear within the IP ranges provided as assets.
This may indicate that the domain has been hijacked by cybercriminals, who altered the A records associated with the domain, resulting in the domain pointing to a different website such as a Phishing attack. Alternatively, the website may have been legitimately moved to a new hosting provider, a CDN (Content Distribution Network) may host company's website on a new location, or the domain has expired.
alerts.details:
The domain is pointing to 3 suspected IP addresses, the details of which are provided below.
%elements%Following is a current screenshot of the site.
alerts.recommendation:
We recommend investigating whether the suspected IP addresses associated with the domain are legitimately used by company or its service providers. If the IP addresses are unfamiliar, we recommend checking whether the domain has expired.
If the domain is still owned by company, but it is pointing to an unfamiliar IP address, we recommend investigating the site now pointed to by the domain to determine the nature and severity of the threat. If a threat is identified, it is recommended to contact the domain registrar.
The details of the hosting providers that control the IP addresses are also provided in the details above in the event you wish to attempt to takedown the site.

alerts.title: 11 Corporate E-mail Addresses Found via Search Engine - company.com
alerts.description:
IntelFinder has identified 11 company E-mail addresses which can be found via search engines.
Threat actors use search engines in order to harvest E-mail addresses of employees during the reconnaissance stage in order to identify potential victims of spear phishing and other types of scams.
This finding does not indicate that the E-mail addresses were compromised in any way. However, it is important to note that the employees who use these addresses are more susceptible to receiving threats via E-mail.
alerts.details:
IMPORTANT NOTICE: Please note that websites may contain vulnerabilities that can put your device, network and organization at risk. If you need to access the URLs below, we recommend doing so from a secure device that is not connected to the rest of the organization. Access the URLs at your own risk.
%elements%
alerts.recommendation:
As the above E-mail addresses are discoverable to attackers who are performing reconnaissance on company, and as some reconnaissance tools are known to look for corporate E-mails using the same techniques we have used to extract the addresses above, the employees using these E-mail addresses should be considered at a higher risk of receiving E-mail threats. We recommend ensuring that the employees recently underwent cyber risk awareness training and that they are familiar with potential cyber threats.

If you prefer the E-mail addresses above would not be discoverable to threat actors, consider reaching out to the website owners.
